er bubbles onto mixing bowl lid while pasta is cooking, add <b>1 tsp oil<b> or butter to the cooking water to reduce frothing.","Pasta that is cooked al dente is tender but still firm to the bite.","The heat of the cooked pasta will partially cook and thicken the egg, so it is important the pasta is still hot when adding the egg mixture to the serving bowl.","To ensure the eggs are not overcooked and the sauce is creamy, in <b>step 6<b> you can rinse the mixing bowl in cold water to cool it off before adding the eggs.","Take care, this recipe contains lightly cooked eggs."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","4 portions"]}